4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REQUIRING APPOINTMENT OF THE CLERK OF THE SUPREME
5 COURT; PROVIDING THAT A MAJORITY OF THE SUPREME COURT JUSTICES APPOINT THE CLERK OF
6 THE SUPREME COURT; PROVIDING THAT THE CLERK OF THE SUPREME COURT SERVES AT THE
7 PLEASURE OF THE COURT; ELIMINATING THE ABILITY OF THE CLERK OF THE SUPREME COURT TO
8 APPOINT A DEPUTY CLERK; AMENDING SECTIONS 2-16-111, 2-16-405, 2-16-505, 3-2-401, 13-12-207,
9 AND 13-16-504, MCA; REPEALING SECTION 3-2-406, MCA; AND PROVIDING EFFECTIVE DATES AND AN
10 APPLICABILITY DATE.”
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
13
14 Section 1. Section 2-16-111, MCA, is amended to read:
15 "2-16-111. Residence of officers. (1) The following officers must shall reside and keep their offices
16 at the seat of government: the governor, secretary of state, state auditor, attorney general, superintendent of
17 public instruction, and justices of the supreme court, and clerk of the supreme court.
18 (2) Restrictions upon on the residence of other officers are contained in the chapter or part relating
19 to the respective officers."
20
21 Section 2. Section 2-16-405, MCA, is amended to read:
22 "2-16-405. Salaries of certain elected state officials. (1) The salaries paid to the following elected
23 officials are determined as provided in subsection (2):
24 (a) governor;
25 (b) lieutenant governor;
26 (c) attorney general;
27 (d) state auditor;
28 (e) superintendent of public instruction;
